= Abishek Sankararaman - Research


=== Spatial Birth-Death Wireless Networks
/ Advisor/ [http://www.ma.utexas.edu/users/baccelli/ Prof. François Baccelli]
~~
{}{img_left}{Locations_SBD.pdf}{}{350px}{250px}{IMGLINKTARGET}

In this work, we study a Spatial Birth-Death model of a wireless network which is a new model for ad-hoc wireless network. This model is motivated by the need for having a model of wireless networks capturing both the stochastic interactions in space (through interference) and in time (due to randomness in traffic arrivals). We propose an interacting particle system based model, where particles (which are wireless links) are born in contiuum space, and stay for a duration in space goverened by the local configuration of points present, and then exit the network after completion of a certain file-transfer. We study this particle dynamics to derive explicit conditions for time-ergodicity. We also prove the intuitive result that when the dynamics is stable, the steady state distribution of points in space exhibit a form of statistical clustering. We are currently investigating this model to understand other forms of Informaton-theoretic interactions. 


