=== Smart Grids - State Estimation and Congestion Control
/ Advisor/ [https://sites.google.com/site/muralibalki/research Dr. Balakrishnan (Murali) Narayanaswamy] 
~~
{}{img_left}{SmartGrid.jpg}{}{300px}{250px}{IMGLINKTARGET}
- Research problem was on techniques to reduce congestion in electric distribution grids by a way of scheduling electric loads.
- Congestion control was achieved by first solving the State Estimation problem to estimate the state of the grid (voltages on all nodes), and then using these estimates for control action.
- Formulated the state estimation of smart grid’s distribution system as an inference problem on a probabilistic graph model (factor graph) and solved it by implementing the loopy Belief
propagation (BP) Algorithm.
- Validated the performance of the loopy BP (an approximate algorithm for non-trees) with a convex optimization approach to solving State Estimation .
- Devised a strategy to optimize the electric losses (a congestion metric) in power distribution grids by formulating and solving the scheduling problem via a gradient descent approach motivated by the solutions implemented in computer networks.
